    "name": "Ögonblicksteatern",
    "profile": "[b]Ögonblicksteatern[/b] (The Moment Theatre) was established in Umeå in 1974 and is thus one of Sweden's oldest free theatres.\r\n\r\n[b]Ögonblicksteatern[/b] presents works that address our contemporary society and highlight the areas where it exhibits shortcomings. By exploring the invisible, the undiscovered, what is taboo, and what is often overlooked, they strive to make these themes both accessible and captivating.\r\n\r\n[b]Ögonblicksteatern[/b] aims to present new images of reality through its activities by seeking out what has hitherto been made invisible and unseen. They continuously strive to find new stories to depict on stage. To believe that another reality is possible, new images of reality need to be presented. In addressing accessibility issues, [b]Ögonblicksteatern[/b] has discovered a significant artistic development potential for performing arts. They are focused on highlighting all bodies and thoughts by working with an ensemble of individuals with non-normative and norma",
